race.comment: ELITE BEAU (10) showed his class first-up over 1000m here with an arrogant win. This looks to shape nicely for him and he has stacks of upside. Pike remains in the saddle and while he will have to improve, he looks right up to this grade. Can bring up back-to-back wins. TWISTED STEEL (6) was backed into favouritism in the Max Simmonds last start and could only finish 1.6L away. That form stood up in the Belgravia last weekend in a good push for his chances. Should be close to the speed from an inside barrier and with improvement to come, he'll take beating. ROSTISLAV (7) was a touch surprising in the Max Simmonds when only 0.5L off the winner as a $17 chance. This looks to shape very similarly to last start for him and he can back up that fresh effort. YES QUEEN (8) is better than she showed last start and can sit much closer than she did last time out. Wouldn't surprise to see her turn her form around. LUANA MISS (9) just missed last start and has to be included.
